HEADWORD: Longevous
<hw>Lon*ge"vous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>longaevus</ets>; <ets>longus</ets> long + <ets>aevum</ets>
lifetime, age. See <er>Long</er>, and <er>Age</er>.]</ety> <def>Living a
long time; of great age.</def> <rj><au>Sir T. Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
